				<td colspan="2"><span>I thought about this too at one point...
<br />

<br />
I'm not sure what other guilds do, but our bards in elementals + generally twist...
<br />

<br />
1) PoV : the damage mitigation from the resists is just key on mobs that have nasty procs
<br />
2) Charisma : always
<br />
3) Rizlonas or zek
<br />

<br />
Honestly, the third song is only doing a little bit for the MT, who is relying on weapon procs mostly for aggro.  Proc rate is independent of haste, so it's hard to really say how much benefit he's getting from rizlonas, other than 15 percent on his straight weapon-based DPS (independent of procs).
<br />

<br />
What would you want to add to that which would justify having a second bard in the group?  And considering that some other bard out there is singing mana and a druid or cleric has a warder up... anything else is going into the main buff box and our tanks are frequently very tight on buff space.</span></td>
